{
  "name": "Spiritual Balance",
  "type": "feature",
  "img": "icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You gain the power to harness your inner spirit as a&nbsp;counterbalance against to your physical energy.</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ki Points</strong></span></p>\n<p>You have a maximum number of Ki Points equal to your&nbsp;Stamina Point. When your Stamina Point maximum&nbsp;increases, your Ki Point maximum also increases equally.</p>\n<p><strong>Regaining Ki:</strong> When you spend a Stamina Point you regain&nbsp;a Ki Point. While out of Combat, any Ki Points you spend&nbsp;replenish immediately.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ki Actions</strong></span></p>\n<p>You can spend 1 Ki Point at any time to perform 1 of the&nbsp;activities listed below:</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.0qIBLgRp0aw0VQHd]{Deflect Attack}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.3FER9KEH8Sub1iyH]{Slow Fall}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.p0hOLzK8sotXyxW5]{Uncanny Dodge}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>System Tip:&nbsp;</strong>You can configure custom resource for Ki Points. If you do so you will be able to use that resource in Ki Actions. To create new resource just put its name in \"New Resource\" box on character sheet and configure it. For max charges formula see Details Tab on that <strong>Feature</strong>.</em></p>",
